{{see|Nelly}}
==English==

===Etymology 1===
Shortened from ''Nelly Duff'', for ''puff'', i.e. breath of ''[[life]]''

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɛli|-ɛli]]

====Noun====
'''nelly''' (''not used in the plural'')
# (''[[Cockney rhyming slang]]'') [[Life]].

====Usage note====
*Used only in the phrase '''[[not on your nelly]]'''.

===Etymology 2===
From the woman's name

====Noun====
{{en-noun-reg-y|nell|y}}

# (''derogatory slang'') An [[effeminate]] homosexual man.
# A common name for the giant [[petrels]], [[Macronectes giganteus]] and [[Macronectes halli]]

===Adjective===
{{en-adj-er-y|nell|y}}

#(''slang'') [[Unmanly]], effeminate.

